---
/**
 * Methodology Page - Explains the Hunter research process
 *
 * Transparency page explaining how StackHunt researches and evaluates tools.
 * Critical for building EEAT (Expertise, Authoritativeness, Trustworthiness)
 * when individual human authors are unavailable.
 *
 * @module pages/methodology
 */

import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  meta={{
    title: 'Research Methodology | StackHunt',
    description:
      'Learn how StackHunt builds evidence-backed software intelligence reports with source policy controls, quality gates, and human oversight.',
    canonical: 'https://stackhunt.co/methodology',
  }}
>
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-gradient-to-b from-zinc-950 to-zinc-900">
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="border-b border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950/50 backdrop-blur-sm">
      <div class="container mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 py-8">
        <!-- Breadcrumbs -->
        <nav class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-zinc-500">
          <a href="/" class="hover:text-indigo-400 transition">Home</a>
          <span>/</span>
          <span class="text-zinc-400">Methodology</span>
        </nav>

        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-3">How StackHunt Works</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-zinc-400">
          We publish editorial intelligence reports for software buyers. Reports are source-backed,
          draft-first, and quality-gated before indexing.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 py-12">
      <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[240px_1fr]">
        <!-- Table of Contents (Sticky) -->
        <aside class="hidden lg:block">
          <div class="sticky top-20">
            <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-400 mb-3">On This Page</h2>
            <nav class="space-y-2 text-sm">
              <a href="#hunter" class="block text-zinc-500 hover:text-indigo-400 transition"
                >The Hunter Process</a
              >
              <a href="#research" class="block text-zinc-500 hover:text-indigo-400 transition pl-3"
                >Phase 1: Research</a
              >
              <a href="#analysis" class="block text-zinc-500 hover:text-indigo-400 transition pl-3"
                >Phase 2: Analysis</a
              >
              <a
                href="#persistence"
                class="block text-zinc-500 hover:text-indigo-400 transition pl-3"
                >Phase 3: Persistence</a
              >
              <a href="#sources" class="block text-zinc-500 hover:text-indigo-400 transition"
                >Source Attribution</a
              >
              <a href="#freshness" class="block text-zinc-500 hover:text-indigo-400 transition"
                >Data Freshness</a
              >
              <a href="#limitations" class="block text-zinc-500 hover:text-indigo-400 transition"
                >What We Don't Do</a
              >
            </nav>
          </div>
        </aside>

        <!-- Content -->
        <article
          class="prose prose-invert max-w-none prose-headings:text-zinc-100 prose-p:text-zinc-400 prose-a:text-indigo-400 hover:prose-a:text-indigo-300 prose-strong:text-zinc-200 prose-li:text-zinc-400 prose-h2:border-b prose-h2:border-zinc-800 prose-h2:pb-3 prose-h2:mb-6 prose-h2:scroll-mt-20 prose-h3:scroll-mt-20"
        >
          {/* Content starts */}

          <div class="not-prose my-8 rounded-lg border border-indigo-500/20 bg-indigo-500/10 p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg
                class="h-6 w-6 flex-shrink-0 text-indigo-400"
                fill="none"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke="currentColor"
              >
                <path
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  stroke-width="2"
                  d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
              </svg>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-100">Our Commitment</h3>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400">
                  We optimize for decision usefulness and trust. When evidence is weak or
                  conflicting, we hide sections instead of publishing filler.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h2 id="hunter">The "Hunter" Research Process</h2>

          <p>
            StackHunt uses a three-phase pipeline to research and evaluate tools. The process is
            automated for speed and consistency, then reviewed with editorial guardrails.
          </p>

          <h3 id="research">Phase 1: Research (The Scout)</h3>

          <p>We gather evidence from eligible public sources with strict source-policy controls.</p>

          <div class="not-prose my-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900 p-4">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-zinc-100">Evidence Intake</h4>
              <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-zinc-400">
                <li>• Official docs, help centers, and pricing pages</li>
                <li>• Changelogs, developer references, and status pages</li>
                <li>• Independent technical coverage and public metadata APIs</li>
                <li>• Release and compatibility evidence</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900 p-4">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-zinc-100">Policy & Quality Controls</h4>
              <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-zinc-400">
                <li>• Restricted domains cannot drive generated claims</li>
                <li>• Unsupported comparative or absolute claims are suppressed</li>
                <li>• Sections are publishable only when evidence thresholds are met</li>
                <li>• Draft/noindex is default when confidence is low</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p>
            We prioritize first-party documentation for factual claims. Public discussion signals,
            when used, are aggregated and treated as subjective context.
          </p>

          <h3 id="analysis">Phase 2: Analysis (Two-Pass AI Synthesis)</h3>

          <p>
            Once we've gathered information, we use Google's Gemini 2.0 Flash to analyze it in two
            distinct passes:
          </p>

          <h4>Pass 1: The Librarian (Knowledge Card Extraction)</h4>

          <p>
            The first pass acts as a meticulous fact-checker. It extracts structured, verifiable
            information:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Core features</strong> - What the tool does</li>
            <li><strong>Pricing tiers</strong> - Plans, costs, billing cycles</li>
            <li><strong>Platform support</strong> - Web, mobile, desktop availability</li>
            <li><strong>Integrations</strong> - Connected apps and services</li>
            <li><strong>Company information</strong> - Founded, headquarters, funding stage</li>
            <li><strong>Competitors</strong> - Main alternatives in the market</li>
            <li><strong>Learning curve</strong> - Time to become productive</li>
          </ul>

          <p>This pass focuses on facts, with claim-source binding for traceability.</p>

          <h4>Pass 2: The Architect (Contextual Synthesis)</h4>

          <p>
            The second pass synthesizes a contextual review that goes beyond the spec sheet. It
            wears three "hats" to provide different perspectives:
          </p>

          <div class="not-prose my-6 space-y-4">
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900 p-4">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div
                  class="flex h-10 w-10 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-blue-500/10"
                >
                  <svg
                    class="h-5 w-5 text-blue-400"
                    fill="none"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                  >
                    <path
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"
                      stroke-width="2"
                      d="M12 8c-1.657 0-3 .895-3 2s1.343 2 3 2 3 .895 3 2-1.343 2-3 2m0-8c1.11 0 2.08.402 2.599 1M12 8V7m0 1v8m0 0v1m0-1c-1.11 0-2.08-.402-2.599-1"
                    ></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <div class="flex-1">
                  <h5 class="font-semibold text-zinc-100">The Budget Analyst</h5>
                  <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-zinc-400">
                    Explains the total cost of ownership without judgment. Identifies cost drivers,
                    one-time fees, commitment terms, and when the premium tier becomes worth it. No
                    "gotcha" language - just facts about how the bill works.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900 p-4">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div
                  class="flex h-10 w-10 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-purple-500/10"
                >
                  <svg
                    class="h-5 w-5 text-purple-400"
                    fill="none"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                  >
                    <path
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"
                      stroke-width="2"
                      d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z"
                    ></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <div class="flex-1">
                  <h5 class="font-semibold text-zinc-100">Observed Usage Patterns</h5>
                  <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-zinc-400">
                    Captures likely fit, friction points, and operational caveats. Subjective
                    insights are framed as reported patterns, not universal facts.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900 p-4">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div
                  class="flex h-10 w-10 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-green-500/10"
                >
                  <svg
                    class="h-5 w-5 text-green-400"
                    fill="none"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                  >
                    <path
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"
                      stroke-width="2"
                      d="M9.663 17h4.673M12 3v1m6.364 1.636l-.707.707M21 12h-1M4 12H3m3.343-5.657l-.707-.707m2.828 9.9a5 5 0 117.072 0l-.548.547A3.374 3.374 0 0014 18.469V19a2 2 0 11-4 0v-.531c0-.895-.356-1.754-.988-2.386l-.548-.547z"
                    ></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <div class="flex-1">
                  <h5 class="font-semibold text-zinc-100">The Human Verdict</h5>
                  <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-zinc-400">
                    A plain-English summary in "Coffee Shop Speak" - no corporate jargon like
                    "seamless," "empowers," or "robust." Just honest, clear language about what this
                    tool actually does and who it's best for.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p>
            Every pro and con includes three pieces of metadata for legal protection and
            transparency:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>source_url</strong> - The exact URL where this claim is supported</li>
            <li>
              <strong>source_type</strong> - Official, independent editorial, or community-derived signal
            </li>
            <li><strong>claim_type</strong> - Fact (verifiable) or opinion (subjective)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 id="persistence">Phase 3: Persistence (Draft-First Publishing)</h3>

          <p>After analysis, we don't immediately publish. Instead, we:</p>

          <ol>
            <li><strong>Create a draft review</strong> - Every review starts unpublished</li>
            <li>
              <strong>Upsert the tool</strong> - Add to our database with metadata and knowledge card
            </li>
            <li><strong>Link to sources</strong> - Store all citation URLs for verification</li>
            <li><strong>Human verification</strong> - Our team reviews before publishing</li>
          </ol>

          <p>This draft-first workflow prevents thin or risky content from shipping by default.</p>

          <h2 id="sources">Source Attribution & Legal Protection</h2>

          <p>
            Every claim on StackHunt is linked to its source. We classify sources into three
            categories to help you assess credibility:
          </p>

          <div class="not-prose my-6 space-y-3">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3 rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900 p-3">
              <div
                class="flex h-8 w-8 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded bg-green-500/10"
              >
                <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-400">OFF</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="font-medium text-zinc-100">Official Sources</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-zinc-400">
                  The tool's own website, blog, documentation, or official announcements. Highest
                  authority for factual claims about features and pricing.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex items-start gap-3 rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900 p-3">
              <div
                class="flex h-8 w-8 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded bg-blue-500/10"
              >
                <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-400">EDI</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="font-medium text-zinc-100">Editorial Sources</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-zinc-400">
                  Independent technical publications and analysis. Useful for context, but lower
                  authority than first-party product documentation.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex items-start gap-3 rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900 p-3">
              <div
                class="flex h-8 w-8 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded bg-purple-500/10"
              >
                <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-purple-400">COM</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="font-medium text-zinc-100">Community Sources</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-zinc-400">
                  Public practitioner discussions can inform friction patterns. These are subjective
                  and do not override official documentation for factual claims.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h2 id="freshness">Data Freshness Policy</h2>

          <p>
            Software changes fast. Pricing updates, features get added, companies get acquired.
            Here's how we keep information current:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Verification dates</strong> - Every tool page shows when it was last verified
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Stale data alerts</strong> - Older volatile fields are flagged for re-verification
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Community verification</strong> - Users can report outdated information, which automatically
              queues the tool for re-research
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Automatic re-hunts</strong> - High-traffic tools are periodically re-researched
              to ensure accuracy
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2 id="limitations">What We Don't Do</h2>

          <p>Transparency includes being clear about our limitations:</p>

          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>We don't claim universal truth</strong> - We publish evidence-backed editorial analysis,
              not absolute judgments.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>We don't republish third-party posts</strong> - We summarize signals and preserve
              citation links; we do not mirror long-form community content.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>We don't rely on restricted review aggregation</strong> - If source policy blocks
              a domain from ingestion, it cannot drive generated claims.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>We can't guarantee 100% accuracy</strong> - We verify everything we can, but software
              changes rapidly and sources can be outdated or incorrect. If you spot an error, please let
              us know.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Report Inaccuracies</h2>

          <p>
            Found something wrong? We take corrections seriously. Every report is reviewed, and if
            we confirm an error, we'll update the content and re-verify the tool.
          </p>

          <p>
            <a
              href="/corrections"
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-indigo-500 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white hover:bg-indigo-600 transition no-underline"
            >
              Submit a correction
              <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  stroke-width="2"
                  d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"></path>
              </svg>
            </a>
          </p>

          <hr class="my-8" />

          <div class="rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900 p-6">
            <h3 class="mt-0 text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-100">Questions About Our Process?</h3>
            <p class="mb-0 text-sm text-zinc-400">
              We're happy to clarify how we research tools, verify information, or handle
              corrections. Our methodology is designed to be transparent and continuously improving.
            </p>
          </div>

          <p class="text-sm text-zinc-500">
            Last updated: {
              new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', {
                month: 'long',
                day: 'numeric',
                year: 'numeric',
              })
            }
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <style>
    html {
      scroll-behavior: smooth;
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
